Agreement signed in Ethiopia’s
capital, Addis Ababa, by 2 countries’ representatives,  African
Union  says in e-mailed statement.
*2 other crossings to be opened during “second phase”:
agreement
*Joint committee to hold next meeting in South Sudan’s capital,
Juba, on May 22
*NOTE: The two nations are making post-secession arrangements
after South Sudan gained independence from Sudan in July 2011  To contact the reporter on this story:
